"In fact, @henryiii, what's the use-case that made you create this method? No `Particle` property is set-able, after all. I would be tempted to simply remove it.\n\nAll particle properties are settable. But the point of this was to make an empty particle to indicate a failure or missing particle.\n\nI've just tried again: some properties are settable, others such as charge and name aren't.\r\n\r\nThen a better action would be to make settable what makes sense, and keep the \"empty\" particle for sitations as you mention. Fine by me.\n\nGenerated properties are not settable, but some of them maybe could be. Charge is automatic based on PID, for example, so can't be set. Name is also derived.\n\n(Everything in the constructor is settable later)"